Hi,
On Thu, 10 Feb 2000 21:25:49 -0500, willy@thepuffingroup.com said:
> Ted, one thing we didn't discuss was handling capabilities in much the
> same way as you proposed for ACLs --- a large number of programs want
> very similar capability sets.  
If you are serious about adding some form of ACL support, then doing
DMAPI at the same time would be a great benefit.  DMAPI (the Data
Migration API) has an optional (but highly desirable) interface for
storing arbitrary migration information alongside inodes, under
application control.
--Stephen
